         <sourceDesc>
            <msDesc>
               <msIdentifier>
                  <idno type="invno">P.Oslo inv. 1672</idno>
               </msIdentifier>
               <msContents>
                  <summary>The text is a petition or hypomnema addressed to the epistates Artemon by an unknown person concerning two sanctuaries, an ibis-temple and a shrine of Isis. Mention is also made of a kleros (military allotment) and the addressee is asked to write to the oikonomos Petosiris. The overall meaning and most of the details remain obscure because of the fragmentary state of the papyrus.</summary>
                  <msItem>
                     <note type="general">Pub. status: Recto, the Verso is blank</note>
                     <textLang mainLang="grc">Greek</textLang>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
               <physDesc>
                  <objectDesc>
                     <supportDesc>
                        <support>1 papyrus ; 13.5 x 14.5 cm.</support>
                        <condition>
                           <ab type="conservation">The fragment is extracted from mummy-cartonnage and is probably from the same cartonnage as P.Oslo inv. 1669. The text is written against the fibres on the recto side. A kollema is visible between 1.2 and 1.3. No doubt the original roll was some 30 cm high, which means that more than half of the text is irretrievably lost.</ab>
                        </condition>
                     </supportDesc>
                     <layoutDesc>
                        <layout>
                           <ab type="lines">11</ab>
